						<div class="postbody">I don't think that's really conceptual, that's more like a practical suggestion for implementation, though it differs from the hardware implementations I'm familiar with:<br /><br />- The powerpak has a 1MHz timer, but it does not use IRQ. It is polled.<br />- The TNS-HFC3 uses NMI, so it doesn't have a 1MHz timer.<br />- CopyNES NSF playback has a timer, but it's polled as well.</div>

